title: House 1
description: A haven of red laterite tiles and cool, natural wood, this Kerala-style house rises gracefully against the lush greenery. The distinctive sloping roof, perfect for heavy monsoon rains, extends generously, casting a cool shade over the expansive verandah below. Ornate wooden pillars support the roof, offering a glimpse of the craftsmanship that defines this architectural style.
